    "body": "> Which actions are you thinking should show up in the notification area? I thought about this at one point, but figured it would make the notification area too busy with messages.\n\nEspecially action that have no immediate visible effect, or confusing one, cut and delete mostly, copy also.\nAs notification can have a click function registered, I was thinking of making the \"delete\" one last long and click would pop-up \"would you like to undelete\"  (maybe).\n\n> It will be rather non trivial to have the menu items show the keyboard shortcut as the information is determined dynamically in a manner that can't be looked up by action, only by the keypress\n> It would require us to create \"names\" for each action\n\nI think going through the intermediate step of \"names\" for action is necessary, \nFor customising layout you would prefer people to maintain `dict(key->str)` instead of `dict(key->action_object)`.\n"
  },
